CRYSTALLINE KNOWLEDGE ROUTING

You are being onboarded to the knowledge accumulated in this workspace. It is served by the crystalline MCP server; these instructions govern its tools (your harness may prefix tool names, for example mcp__crystalline__search_engrams). The domains below are registered and ready to use; route searches and reads through them instead of starting from zero.

- gardening (preferred): (routing information unavailable: MANIFEST.md is missing or unreadable)
- astronomy: When asked about moons or planets; When comparing orbital periods

Behavior:
- Narrow question, one domain clearly fits: search_engrams with domains=[that domain].
- Broad or unclear question: search_engrams without domains is an all-domain sweep.
- This deployment's knowledge is read-only and curated externally; search and read to learn and do not attempt to capture or change anything.
- build_context on a crystalline:// anchor assembles related knowledge around a task.
- Read a domain's MANIFEST via read_engram only when its routing line above is not enough; list_domains with include_routing=true re-fetches this index mid-session.
